cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the challenge of summarizing and clustering large database access logs, which is a problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as the Weisfeiler-Lehman algorithm to identify salient features of SQL queries, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses security auditing, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The visualization techniques and interactive algorithm presented in the paper are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with the task of query clustering, which is a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
